data.content:
Yes — use `Assert.IsInstanceOfType` to combine the cast and null check, and get a clearer failure message:

```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void Create_ReturnsCorrectHandler()
{
    var factory = new HandlerFactory();

    var handler = Assert.IsInstanceOfType<EmailHandler>(factory.Create("email"));

    Assert.AreEqual("email", handler.Type);
}
```

The generic `Assert.IsInstanceOfType<T>` (MSTest v3+) returns the cast object directly, so you can keep asserting on it. It fails with a descriptive message if the type doesn't match or the value is null — no manual cast needed.
